    "Microsoft's AETHER Committee regularly invites engineers to working groups [99].On the one hand, substructures can make the board more complex and add friction.",
    "On the other hand, they allow for faster decision-making because less people are involved and group discussions tend to be more efficient.",
    "Against this background, we expect that substructures are probably only needed in larger ethics boards (Sect. 4.3).",
